        public java.util.Vector filter(java.lang.Object x,
                      java.lang.Object arg,
                      java.util.Hashtable params)
                        throws LocalSearchException
        Description copied from interface: NeighborhoodFilterIntf
        method will return a Vector of argument objects to be "tried" so as to "expand" or "shrink" the neighborhood defined around the solution arg. The returned Vector will contain objects to be tried, based on the "guiding" object x. For example, in a graph packing application, x might be a set of integers to be removed from the current solution arg (that might also be a set of integers), and then, the resulting vector will contain all the new integers that can be added to the reduced solution.
